Paper: hep-th/0202072

Date: 2002-02-11

Title: Statistical interpretation of Bekenstein entropy for systems with a

stretched horizonAuthors: Oleg Lunin, Samir D. Mathur

Comments: 4 pages, 3 figures, Revtex; comment added in the discussion

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 88 (2002) 211303

For the 2-charge extremal holes in string theory we show that the Bekensteinentropy obtained from the area of the stretched horizon has a statisticalgeometries that differ near r=0 and the stretched horizon cuts off the metricat r=b where these geometries start to differ.